<HEAD>Wintery Weather Sweeps Through Upper Midwest</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Brisk wintry temperatures chilled much of the upper Midwest
today, bringing icy readings to the Dakotas, Iowa and much of
Minnesota and Nebraska.
   Snow was falling over northwest Wisconsin at midnight. But no
measurable snowfall was reported in the 6 hours ending at 2 a.m.
EDT.
   Rain was scattered over northern Indiana, northern Illinois,
western Kansas and eastern Colorado. Rain also reached from
southeast New England and over the central Atlantic states through
South Carolina.
   Midnight temperatures in the 20s and 30s extended across the
Dakotas and northeast Montana, and there were readings in the 30s
and 40s from northern Wisconsin to Minnesota and northern Nebraska.
   Today's forecast called for rain from New England and the upper
Ohio Valley to the central Appalachians and the Middle Atlantic
States; scattered showers and thunderstorms from the southern
Atlantic Coast to central and southern Florida; and showers over
the lower Great Lakes.
   Temperatures were forecast in the 40s from the eastern Dakotas
into the central Plains and from the upper Mississippi Valley
across the upper Great Lakes; in the 70s and 80s from Texas, except
the Panhandle, as well as over the lower Mississippi Valley, the
Gulf Coast and southern Atlantic, from the Southern California
coast to Nevada and eastern sections of Oregon and Washington; in
the 90s to near 105 degrees across the desert Southwest, and in the
50s or 60s across thr rest of the nation.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 15
degrees at Devils Lake, N.D., to 85 degrees at Phoenix.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 61 cloudy; Boston 55 cloudy; Buffalo 47 cloudy;
Charleston, S.C. 68 cloudy; Cincinnati 47 fair; Cleveland 40 fair;
Detroit 42 fair; New York 58 cloudy; Philadelphia 59 cloudy;
Pittsburgh 43 fair; Portland, Maine 51 cloudy; Washington 59 rain.
   _Central: Bismarck 26 fair; Chicago 49 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
57 fair; Denver 49 fair; Des Moines 42 fair; Indianapolis 40 fair;
Kansas City 57 partly cloudy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 38 fair;
Nashville 50 fair; New Orleans 67 partly cloudy; St. Louis 49 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 59 fair; Anchorage 44 rain; Las Vegas 75
partly cloudy; Los Angeles 63 partly cloudy; Phoenix 85 fair; Salt
Lake City 55 fair; San Diego 64 foggy; San Francisco 54 fair;
Seattle 55 foggy.
   _Canada: Montreal 41 fair; Toronto 45 partly cloudy.
