<HEAD>Policeman Killed While Guarding Government Office</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MADRID, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two men and a woman stormed a government
office in central Madrid today, shooting and killing a policeman
and injuring three other people, police said.
   The assailants took the policeman's gun as he stood guard
outside the ground-floor office, then used it to shoot the officer
twice in the head, Spanish National Radio reported. The shooting
took place at 9:40 a.m. on the busy street of Santa Engracia,
police said.
