<1ST_LINE>r a PM-FurloughAttack     10-04 0332</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Furlough Attack,0338</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Prison Inmate on Furlough Accused of Attacking Former Girlfriend</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SPRINGFIELD, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A state prison inmate accused of
attacking his former girlfriend while on furlough from a halfway
house was ordered held in lieu of $500,000 bail after pleading
innocent to assault charges.
   ``We have some serious problems with the prison furlough
program,'' Hampden County District Attorney Matthew J. Ryan Jr.
said Monday after the arraignment. ``The police are even more upset
than we are and the victims can't understand what is going on.''
   It was the third time within a year, he said, that a prisoner
from Hampden County has been arrested while on a furlough or on an
early release program.
   A furlough program for first-degree murder convicts in
Massachusetts was canceled earlier this year following the
kidnapping and assault of a Maryland couple by an inmate who was on
furlough. Gov. Michael S. Dukakis has come under fire from his GOP
presidential rival, George Bush, because of the furloughs of
murderers.
   In the recent case, Isaac Aycox, 37, pleaded innocent to charges
of assault and battery, armed breaking and entering, malicious
damage and threatening to murder his former girlfriend. He also
pleaded innocent to charges of assault and battery on a police
officer and trying to steal a police car while at police
headquarters, authorities said.
   Aycox had been serving concurrent 8-to-20-year terms for armed
robbery and assault. He would have been eligible for parole within
weeks and was to have completed his prison sentence in March,
according to Kathy Ayers, a spokeswoman for the state prison system.
   ``This was his first furlough,'' she said. ``He was working
during the week and checking in at night.''
   Early Sunday, Aycox allegedly appeared at the former
girlfriend's home. When she refused to see him, he smashed the
windows of her car with a chunk of concrete, police said. Then he
broke down the door of her apartment, struck her and threatened to
kill her, McGovern said.
