<1ST_LINE>u a PM-FinancierAttacked     10-04 0286</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Financier Attacked,0296</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Financier And John Wayne's Daughter Attacked</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEWPORT BEACH, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A wealthy financier and his
companion, a daughter of the late actor John Wayne, were tied up
and beaten in a daytime attack by two men who slashed the man's
Achilles' tendons.
   ``This attack was meant as a warning or message, and exactly
what that message is we don't know yet,'' said police Detective
Sgt. Mike Jackson. ``We've got a million angles to explore on this
case.''
   Roger Luby, 52, and Aissa Wayne, 32, were attacked Monday
morning by two men who followed them inside the electric gates at
the mortgage financier's multimillion-dollar home, said Jackson.
   The attackers tied up Luby and Ms. Wayne, the eldest daughter of
Pilar and John Wayne, Jackson said. Then they beat both and slashed
the Achilles tendons behind each of Luby's feet.
   However, they were released after being treated at Hoag Memorial
Hospital Presbyterian, family members said.
   Nothing was stolen, Jackson said.
   Both victims are going through divorces. Ms. Wayne is embroiled
in a custody battle over her 1-year-old daughter.
   Luby also is involved in real estate litigation and bankruptcy
proceedings involving his purchase of the Broadway Department Store
in Los Angeles, the Orange County Register reported, citing court
records, friends and business associates.
   Ms. Wayne was in seclusion with relatives after the attack.
   ``She's home with us,'' said her brother Ethan. ``She's going to
be fine. But she's very scared about all this.''
   Her estranged husband, Dr. Thomas A. Gionis, an orthopedic
surgeon, said he was dismayed by the attack.
   ``I can't believe it,'' he said. ``We still communicate a lot
even though we're not together. Who would do such a thing and why?''
</TEXT>
