<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Centenarians,0101</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>China has 3,765 Centenarians</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   China has 3,765 people who are at least 100 years
old among its population of 1 billion, the official Xinhua News
Agency said Tuesday.
   The report said there are 228 Chinese between the ages of 110
and 119 and 36 who are older than 120. It said 2,657 of the
centenarians are women.
   The Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, the remote desert area of
far western China populated mainly by Central Asian Moslems, has
the highest rate of centenarians, with 66 out of every 1 million
people, according to the report.
