<HEAD>Galbraith, Greene Granted Honorary Doctorates by Moscow University</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mikhail S. Gorbachev's alma mater, Moscow State
University, awarded honorary doctorates Tuesday to American
economist John Kenneth Galbraith and British writer Graham Greene.
   Galbraith, a professor at Harvard University, was honored for
``his services in the development of sciences and the humanities,''
the official Tass news agency said.
   Greene's doctorate is a sign of ``his outstanding services in
the field of literature and in the strengthening of friendly
contacts with the Soviet Union,'' Tass said.
   It said the certificates were presented to Galbraith and Greene
by Anatoly Logunov, rector of Moscow State University and a member
of the Academy of Sciences.
   Gorbachev, a native of the southern Russian region of Stavropol,
studied law at Moscow State University and met his wife Raisa
there. Both graduated in 1954.
