<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Sex Crackdown,0106</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Confiscate Cars of Prostitutes' Customers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police have begun confiscating cars belonging to
prostitutes' clients in a new strategy that forces the customers to
either take a cab or public transportation home _ or call a friend
or spouse for a ride.
   The crackdown began Monday in an effort to control the city's
longstanding problem with prostitution.
   Under the program, officers who arrest prostitutes' customers
will keep their cars even after the offenders are released.
   Police said they will ask for court permission to keep the
vehicles permanently.
   Several vehicles have already been seized, police said.
