<HEAD>House OKs Ban on New Dams in Parks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Legislation to generally prohibit the
construction of new dams in national parks and national monuments
was passed by the House on Tuesday.
   The bill, sent to the Senate by a 405-12 vote, also would apply
to new dams that would inundate parks and monuments. The National
Park Service could waive the bans if it considered a particular dam
necessary.
