<1ST_LINE>r a AM-FinancierAttacked     10-04 0300</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Financier Attacked,0310</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Businessman, John Wayne's Daughter Attacked</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEWPORT BEACH, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A wealthy financier and a daughter
of the late actor John Wayne were tied up and beaten in a daytime
attack by two men, and police on Tuesday said no clear motive for
the attack had been determined.
   Roger Luby, 52, and Aissa Wayne, 32, were attacked Monday
morning by two men who followed them into Luby's mansion.
   ``It looks like she was in the wrong place at the wrong time,''
said Detective Sgt. Mike Jackson. ``It was meant as a message to
him. As of now, we don't know what that message is.''
   Ms. Wayne told The Los Angeles Times on Tuesday that one of the
attackers said: ``You're messing with the wrong guy. Next time
we'll kill you.''
   The attackers tied up Luby and Ms. Wayne, the eldest daughter of
the late actor and Pilar Wayne.
   ``They grabbed her hair and beat her face against the
concrete,'' said Mrs. Wayne. ``Imagine the horror of somebody
telling you, `I'm gonna kill you if you say one word.' ''
   The assailant tried to cut Luby's right Achilles' tendon, but
failed to slice through it, police spokesman Greg Armstrong said.
Luby is a tennis player, which may be why the attacker tried to cut
his tendon, Jackson said.
   Nothing was stolen during the attack, Jackson said. ``Obviously,
somebody hired these guys,'' Jackson said. ``They went in, did
their thing and got out.''
   Ms. Wayne and Luby are going through divorces.
   Luby also is reportedly involved in real estate litigation and
bankruptcy proceedings involving his purchase of the Broadway
Department Store in Los Angeles.
   Luby declined to discuss the attack.
   ``As of now I'm all right, but on advice of counsel I can't say
anything,'' he said Tuesday.
</TEXT>
