<HEAD>EEC Steel Ouput Up in July, August</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steel output in the European Economic
Community totaled 20.7 million metric tons in July and August, up
9.5 percent from a year ago, the EEC statistics agency reported
Tuesday.
   Eurostat said that for the first half of 1988 new orders for
ordinary steel rose 13 percent from 1987, to 58 million tons.
