<1ST_LINE>r f PM-GTERelocation     10-04 0171</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-GTE Relocation,0179</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>GTE Moving General Offices Of Telephone Operating Group</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   GTE Corp. is moving the general office of its
Telephone Operating Group from Stamford, Conn., but will maintain
corporate headquarters in the Connecticut city, the company said
today.
   James Broadhead, the president of the telephone group, told
headquarters employees today that a new location for the group has
not been selected.
   Speculation on the new location has centered on the Dallas-Fort
Worth area. About 300 of the roughly 1,000 people employed by GTE
in Stamford are part of the Telephone Operating Group, said
Geoffrey Pickard, vice president for public affairs in GTE's
Products and Systems Group.
   GTE has repeatedly denied that the headquarters of the entire
corporation would be moved from Stamford and did so again today.
   The Dallas Morning News, quoting unnamed sources, reported today
that GTE was moving its entire corporate headquarters to
Dallas-Fort Worth after eyeing sites in Tampa, Fla., Thousand Oaks,
Calif., and Westfield, Ind.
   ``It's absolutely not true,'' Pickard said.
</TEXT>
