<1ST_LINE>r f PM-LTVSteel-Sale     10-04 0185</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-LTV Steel-Sale,0193</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>LTV Corp. Putting Steel Bar Division Up For Sale</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CANTON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   LTV Corp. said today it plans to sell LTV
Steel Co.'s Ohio-based bar division, in line with its
reorganization under federal bankruptcy laws.
   Raymond A. Hay, LTV's chairman and chief executive officer, said
the company wants its steel division to concentrate on flat rolled
and tubular products.
   ``We have concluded that LTV Steel must focus its resources on
its large, modern flat-rolled facilities in order to maintain a
leadership position in production of high quality, value added
steels for critical engineering applications,'' Hay said.
   LTV Steel, based in Cleveland, is a branch of Dallas-based LTV
Corp., a diversified manufacturing company also involved in
aerospace, defense and energy products.
   Hay said the company's third-quarter results will include a
substantial charge against earnings as a result of today's move.
   The bar division, located in Canton, Ohio, employs about 5,400
workers who produce approximately 1.2 million tons of steel
annually.
   LTV Corp. has hired Shearson Lehman Hutton Inc. to assist in
finding a qualified buyer for the bar division, officials said.
</TEXT>
